{
    "publish_date": "2011-12-12T23:04:53.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT2M47S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "We have built a virtual, slow-motion camera,", 
            "dur": "3.029", 
            "start": "0.033"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "where we can see photons, or light particles, moving", 
            "dur": "4.943", 
            "start": "3.062"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "through space. Now you have seen Doc Edgerton&#39;s", 
            "dur": "2.065", 
            "start": "8.005"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "pictures of a bullet through an apple.", 
            "dur": "2.999", 
            "start": "10.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But photons travel about a million times faster", 
            "dur": "4.961", 
            "start": "13.069"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "than bullets. So our camera can see these photons,", 
            "dur": "4.064", 
            "start": "18.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or bullets of light, traveling through space.", 
            "dur": "3.962", 
            "start": "22.094"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We use a very regular pulsed light source", 
            "dur": "2.026", 
            "start": "26.056"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and a camera, that is not one camera, but an array", 
            "dur": "3.95", 
            "start": "28.082"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of five hundred sensors, each triggered at a", 
            "dur": "2.988", 
            "start": "32.032"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "trillionth-of-a second-delay.", 
            "dur": "2.004", 
            "start": "35.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, even though each of our sensors is slow, we", 
            "dur": "3.025", 
            "start": "37.024"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "can still capture fast movie.", 
            "dur": "2.959", 
            "start": "40.049"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m standing next to our laboratory setup here.", 
            "dur": "3.004", 
            "start": "43.008"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is our camera, objectives in the front here.", 
            "dur": "3.04", 
            "start": "46.012"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The body of the camera is much larger than what", 
            "dur": "3.957", 
            "start": "49.052"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you would expect from a regular camera,", 
            "dur": "1.054", 
            "start": "53.009"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like the one over here.", 
            "dur": "1.971", 
            "start": "54.063"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Our light source is a titanium-sapphire laser", 
            "dur": "2.977", 
            "start": "56.034"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that&#39;s over here, and emits a beam of very, very", 
            "dur": "2.079", 
            "start": "59.011"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "short pulses, and those pulses are then directed to", 
            "dur": "3.941", 
            "start": "61.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the seam [pause] with these mirrors.", 
            "dur": "5.051", 
            "start": "65.031"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, our camera only sees one dimension", 
            "dur": "4.004", 
            "start": "70.082"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so it makes a fast movie, but it makes a fast movie", 
            "dur": "2.929", 
            "start": "74.086"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of one line of the scene only", 
            "dur": "2.034", 
            "start": "77.015"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And in order to fix that, we have these two", 
            "dur": "2.017", 
            "start": "79.049"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "mirrors here. We look at the scene via these two", 
            "dur": "2.992", 
            "start": "81.066"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "mirrors, and when we rotate this upper mirror here", 
            "dur": "3.021", 
            "start": "84.058"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we actually see different lines of the scene.", 
            "dur": "2.974", 
            "start": "87.079"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, what&#39;s happening is, the camera keeps taking", 
            "dur": "3.031", 
            "start": "90.053"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "images and we very slowly rotate this mirror", 
            "dur": "3.935", 
            "start": "93.084"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to scan our field of view across the entire scene.", 
            "dur": "4.028", 
            "start": "97.019"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And because all of our pulses look the same,", 
            "dur": "2.05", 
            "start": "101.047"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we can, in the end, go and combine all of these", 
            "dur": "3.93", 
            "start": "103.097"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "images that we took to get one complete movie", 
            "dur": "2.988", 
            "start": "107.027"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of the scene.", 
            "dur": "1.077", 
            "start": "110.015"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Such a camera may be useful in medical imaging", 
            "dur": "2.99", 
            "start": "111.092"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in industrial or scientific use, and in the future", 
            "dur": "4.978", 
            "start": "114.082"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "even for consumer photography.", 
            "dur": "2.035", 
            "start": "119.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In medical imaging, now we can do ultrasound with", 
            "dur": "2.992", 
            "start": "121.095"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "light, because we can analyze how light will scatter", 
            "dur": "3.984", 
            "start": "124.087"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "one-dimentionally inside the body.", 
            "dur": "2.933", 
            "start": "128.071"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In industrial imaging, one can use the scattered light", 
            "dur": "5.088", 
            "start": "131.004"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to analyze defects in materials.", 
            "dur": "3.005", 
            "start": "136.092"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And in consumer photography, we are always", 
            "dur": "3.963", 
            "start": "139.097"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "fascinated with creating lighting effects that appear", 
            "dur": "3.983", 
            "start": "143.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to come from very sophisticated light sources.", 
            "dur": "2.98", 
            "start": "147.043"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But, because we can watch photons seemingly", 
            "dur": "3.985", 
            "start": "150.023"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "moving through the space, we can analyze the", 
            "dur": "2.053", 
            "start": "154.008"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "transport, the movement, of these photons and", 
            "dur": "2.954", 
            "start": "156.061"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "create new photographs as if we had created", 
            "dur": "3.022", 
            "start": "159.015"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "those expensive light sources in a studio.", 
            "dur": "3.042", 
            "start": "162.037"
        }
    ], 
